    "body": "### Problem\n\n- Reproducible on NVIM v0.11.6\n Opening nvim fails with the following error:\n\n\"noclear\" [New]\nCannot open file \"noclear\"                                                                            \nError detected while processing /usr/share/vim/vim92/ftplugin.vim:\nline    1:                                                                                            \nE480: No match: 9script\n\nfull error available in this gist: https://gist.github.com/DisturbingShibboleth/d55f5f1e4dcbd30ecac6891ec2991f67\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean` and `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua` both cause the same error \n`env -i TERM=ansi-256color \"$(which nvim)\"` causes neovim to open with:\n\n<img width=\"655\" height=\"513\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5efb2232-4a21-47de-8a7f-5e32703b0f8b\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nexpect neovim to open\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.6\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.2.204\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.46.2, st 0.8.4\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty, st-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nInstalled on Arch Linux via  pacman (x86_64 Extra)",
